text.section:
The report shall be made under oath and shall include:
The name, if known, and last known address, if any, of each person who appears from the records of the holder to be the owner of any property valued at $100 or more and presumed abandoned under this subtitle;
In case of unclaimed funds of an insurance corporation, the full name of the insured, annuitant, principal, or claimant, and the last known address according to the insurance corporation's records;
The nature and identifying number, if any, or description of the property and the amount which appears from the records to be due, except that items valued at less than $100 each may be reported in the aggregate;
The date when the property became payable, demandable, or returnable, and the date of the last transaction with the owner with respect to the property; and
Any other information which the Administrator prescribes by rule as necessary for the administration of this title.
